details: Going Places is a 1974 French comedy-drama film co-written and directed by Bertrand Blier, and based on his own novel. Its original title is Les Valseuses, which translates into English as 'the waltzers', a vulgar French slang term for 'the testicles'. It stars Miou-Miou, Gérard Depardieu and Patrick Dewaere.
